Business Brief -- Nerco Inc.:
   Firm Posts Higher Earnings,
   But Sees First-Period Loss
Nerco is 82%-owned by PacifiCorp, based in Portland.
   Nerco, which has interests in coal, oil, natural gas and
precious metals, posted fourth-quarter net income of $54.5
million, or $1.39 a share, on revenue of $290.6 million,
compared with year-earlier net of $22.1 million, or 56 cents
a share, on revenue of $255 million.
   The quarter included an after-tax gain of $36.1 million,
or 92 cents a share, from the sale of a 25-year natural gas
supply contract and a gain of $3.3 million, or eight cents a
share, related to the settlement of a disputed coal supply
agreement.